docreader.range.paragraph.characterRun

Class FakeFieldHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • docreader.range.paragraph.characterRun.CharacterRunRawProcessor
      • docreader.range.paragraph.characterRun.FakeFieldHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CharacterRunReaderGeneric, Destructible

    public class FakeFieldHandler
extends CharacterRunRawProcessor
    Processes textual links, which are not declared as such (i.e. they are not embedded in a Word field)

    similar to ParagraphReader.FieldDataHandler

    Author:
    Moritz Dorka

        Ordinary constructor
        Parameters:
        traceabilityLinkerNonQualified - handle to the global traceability linker for non qualified requirements
        startOffset - startOffset from where to start reading the paragraph text (0-based; relevant for fake list paragraphs)
        requirement - requirement where to store the links
        lastWordOfPreviousParagraph - last word of the previously processed paragraph (used for links which span several paragraphs)

        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the arguments is null
